{"_id": "5595e2e21f8a4ae4", "name": "Arcane Expansion – Mishaps & Corruption", "type": "text", "img": "icons/svg/scroll.svg", "system": {}, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "folder": null, "sort": 0, "pages": [{"_id": "801a3684067c41c8", "name": "Description", "type": "text", "sort": 0, "title": {"show": true, "level": 1}, "text": {"content": "<h1>Arcane Expansion – Mishaps & Corruption</h1><h1>Arcane Expansion – Mishaps & Corruption</h1><p><em>Dragonbane Arcane Expansion reference.</em></p><p><h2>Spell Mishaps</h2></p><p><p><strong>Trigger a mishap check</strong> when: (1) you roll a <strong>Demon (20)</strong> on a spellcasting roll; (2) you cast at <strong>0 WP</strong>; (3) you cast while <strong>Broken</strong>; or (4) you overspend WP.</p></p><p><p>When triggered: resolve the spell (GM may alter), then roll <strong>1d6</strong> on the Universal Mishap Table. If the spell is <strong>Necromancy, Voidmage, or Chronomancy</strong>, also roll on that school’s corruption table.</p></p><p><h3>Universal Mishap Table (1d6)</h3></p><p><ol><li><strong>Backlash:</strong> Take 1d6 damage (type matches spell).</li><li><strong>Drain:</strong> Lose 1d3 additional WP.</li><li><strong>Fracture:</strong> You become <strong>Fractured</strong> (Bane on spellcasting) until a full rest.</li><li><strong>Wild Effect:</strong> Spell affects unintended target/area.</li><li><strong>Fatigue:</strong> You become <strong>Exhausted</strong>.</li><li><strong>Echo:</strong> Spell repeats next round at half strength (GM chooses target if needed).</li></ol></p><p><h3>Corruption Tracks (Optional)</h3></p><p><p>Risk schools (Necromancy/Void/Chrono) gain Corruption Marks on major mishaps. At 3 marks: visible change. At 5: permanent consequence. At 7: transformation or exit.</p></p>", "format": 1}}]}
{"_id": "64861d01f6c74a07", "name": "Arcane Expansion – Fracture Condition", "type": "text", "img": "icons/svg/scroll.svg", "system": {}, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "folder": null, "sort": 0, "pages": [{"_id": "72e7da9a4d814eb8", "name": "Description", "type": "text", "sort": 0, "title": {"show": true, "level": 1}, "text": {"content": "<h1>Arcane Expansion – Fracture Condition</h1><h1>Arcane Expansion – Fracture Condition</h1><p><em>Dragonbane Arcane Expansion reference.</em></p><p><h2>Fracture (Condition)</h2></p><p><p><strong>Fractured</strong> represents magical instability or broken focus.</p></p><p><ul><li><strong>Effect:</strong> You have <strong>Bane on all spellcasting rolls</strong>.</li><li>Does not affect non-magical actions.</li><li>Does not stack.</li></ul></p><p><p><strong>Remove:</strong> A <strong>full rest</strong> removes Fracture. Ritual calm/mending may remove it earlier at GM discretion.</p></p><p><p><em>Optional:</em> If you become Fractured twice in the same scene, the second becomes <strong>Exhausted</strong> instead.</p></p>", "format": 1}}]}
{"_id": "9fc5157955b64e2f", "name": "Arcane Expansion – Grimoires", "type": "text", "img": "icons/svg/scroll.svg", "system": {}, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "folder": null, "sort": 0, "pages": [{"_id": "ab3514241fd94d94", "name": "Description", "type": "text", "sort": 0, "title": {"show": true, "level": 1}, "text": {"content": "<h1>Arcane Expansion – Grimoires</h1><h1>Arcane Expansion – Grimoires</h1><p><em>Dragonbane Arcane Expansion reference.</em></p><p><h2>Grimoires & Learning</h2></p><p><p>Grimoires contain spells and make them easier to learn. They do not cast spells and do not store WP.</p></p><p><ul><li>A grimoire lists which spells it teaches.</li><li>Studying a grimoire during downtime may allow learning a contained spell (GM sets time/roll).</li><li>Some grimoires grant <strong>Boon</strong> on learning or reduce learning time.</li><li>Forbidden grimoires (Necromancy/Void/Chrono) may impose <strong>corruption</strong> or <strong>fatigue</strong>.</li></ul></p>", "format": 1}}]}
{"_id": "c2ec304b860e4524", "name": "Expanded Dragonbane – Import & Cleanup Tools", "type": "JournalEntry", "img": "icons/svg/book.svg", "system": {}, "pages": [{"_id": "1ae0aa923c4340bc", "name": "Instructions", "type": "text", "sort": 0, "title": {"show": true, "level": 1}, "text": {"content": "<h1>Expanded Dragonbane – Import & Cleanup Tools</h1>\n<p>This module ships with two GM tools to help you populate your WORLD folders without renaming spells/items.</p>\n\n<h2>What this does</h2>\n<ul>\n  <li>Creates an <strong>Expanded Dragonbane</strong> folder in your <strong>Items</strong> directory.</li>\n  <li>Creates subfolders that match Dragonbane conventions:</li>\n</ul>\n<pre>\nExpanded Dragonbane\n  Spells\n    Animism / Elementalism / Mentalism / Necromancy / Chronomancy / Voidmage / General\n  Items\n    Weapons / Armor / Helmets / Artifacts / Items\n</pre>\n\n<h2>Import (recommended)</h2>\n<ol>\n  <li>Run the macro: <strong>@UUID[Compendium.dragonbane-arcane-expansion.macros.Macro.21c6e14019ba473a]{DBAE – Import to Expanded Dragonbane Folders}</strong></li>\n  <li>The macro imports from the module compendiums into your WORLD folders and sorts spells by <strong>Rank</strong> then <strong>Name</strong>.</li>\n  <li>It skips duplicates by name within each destination folder.</li>\n</ol>\n\n<h2>Cleanup (if you imported the wrong version)</h2>\n<ol>\n  <li>Run the macro: <strong>@UUID[Compendium.dragonbane-arcane-expansion.macros.Macro.ff1bfd73c2f8419d]{DBAE – Cleanup Imported DBAE Content}</strong></li>\n  <li>This deletes WORLD copies that were imported from this module (based on <code>flags.core.sourceId</code>).</li>\n  <li>It does <em>not</em> delete the module compendiums.</li>\n</ol>\n\n<h2>Tip</h2>\n<p>Module compendiums are libraries. Your WORLD folders are where you keep your campaign’s working copies.</p>\n", "format": 1}}], "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}}
